      <symbol code="205" id="31" name="Cave" type="1">
        <description>A cave is represented by the same symbol as a rocky pit. In this case the symbol shall be orientated to point up the slope as indicated opposite. This symbol should generally not be used in urban areas. The centre of gravity of the symbol marks the opening.

&lt;span style="color:magenta"&gt;Controls may not be placed inside caves!&lt;/span&gt;</description>
